This shell script finds any .mp3 files recursively in the directory_name/path given. 
If no path is given as the command-line argument, it takes current directory(.) as the directory_name.
It REMOVES ALL THE EXISTING TAGS(both v1 and v2) of any .mp3 file found and recreates id3v1 and id3v2 tags.
It assigns Album the directory name, Title the file name with ".mp3", other "."s clipped and charecters lowered(converted to lowercase).
This package uses id3v2/id3tool command-line id3 tag editing tool.


